{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h3><a href=\"https://itp.nyu.edu/physcomp/labs/labs-arduino-digital-and-analog/analog-in-with-an-arduino/\">Lab 3</a> documentation</h3>\n<p>A simple circuit which reads a potentiometer (analog input) to control the brightness of an LED.</p>\n<iframe src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/291979246\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" frameborder=\"0\" webkitallowfullscreen mozallowfullscreen allowfullscreen></iframe>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/week-3-analog-in-b4e64fce1b551de7b2559d43a3c3b9f8-5ea44.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 768px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 133.33333333333331%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"analog-in\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/week-3-analog-in-b4e64fce1b551de7b2559d43a3c3b9f8-5ea44.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/week-3-analog-in-b4e64fce1b551de7b2559d43a3c3b9f8-e0edb.jpg 222w,\n/static/week-3-analog-in-b4e64fce1b551de7b2559d43a3c3b9f8-b04ee.jpg 444w,\n/static/week-3-analog-in-b4e64fce1b551de7b2559d43a3c3b9f8-5ea44.jpg 768w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h3>Code</h3>\n<pre><code class=\"language-c\">const int ledPin = 9;\nint analogValue = 0;\nint brightness = 0;\n\nvoid setup() {\n    pinMode(ledPin, OUTPUT);\n}\n\nvoid loop() {\n    analogValue = analogRead(A0);\n    brightness = analogValue / 4;\n    analogWrite(ledPin, brightness);\n}\n</code></pre>","frontmatter":{"date":"26 September 2018","title":"Week 3 - Lab 3 - Analog In with an Arduino"},"fields":{"category":"physical-computing","slug":"/blog/itp/physical-computing/week-3-lab-3/"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/blog/itp/physical-computing/week-3-lab-3/"}}